<br>
I'm 9th level, and heading out beyond the safety of Misty when I get a buffer. I know some basics, like keep See Invis up, camo to med, don't get too awfully low on health if I can help it...but I'm pretty green other than that.<br>
<br>
How much is Snare and Root going to get resisted against people in my level range? What classes are easy to fight, which ones should make me nervous? Are there any good sites with EQ PvP strategies?<br>
<br>
If I can get Snare to stick on someone, I think half the battle is done. At least I can get away if things go bad :-)<br>
<br>
I've got to start getting resist gear too. All I have so far is full patchwork and some crap weapons.<br>
<br>
Oh, and does anyone have any suggestions for shaking hands and that huge adrenaline rush when you're thinking about attacking? Hard to type when your muscles in your arm are locking up from the rush, lol. <p><b>Gallatin</b><p>
<font size=3>Everyone is entitled to their own wrong opinion</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=leadar>Leadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/10/01 4:17:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid PvP tips</span><hr size=1> Lol, Im on SZ too, just started a druid there.  From what Ive seen so far, snare works almost always against other PC's.  I believe that it is considered a debuff.  In the rules, it says that all debuff spells are 50% more likely to stick on other PC's, so use it always I would say.  <br>
<br>
Against wizards one on one, I have used the technique of snaring them, then run run run, to edge of area where their casting range is.  From what I have seen, they can still hit you with a DD, but cant root you in a certain range (this range seems to be approximately the range of your dot line of spells for their dd's-so run out of range, then target them, start hitting your dot spell, and stop going towards them once your dot starts to work).  Let them hit you with ONE DD, run out of range, heal, run back in range, and let them start casting on you again. Take the dmg, run out of range, heal.  You will end up having a little under 1/2 mana on a closely leveled wizard, when he runs oom, then just beat the crap out of him with your weapon and keep him snared, throw a dot on him for good measure.  <br>
<br>
Use your sow, snare, and distance to kill when solo.  Otherwise, when you are in a group, just assist your main tank and snare and blast the target.  If you see a bunch of tanks jump on one of your guys, throw a damage shield on him, and keep that person healed.  There is alot you can do, use it.  In our 20's we get an AOE blind spell, would be good for a sneak attack on a group.  Keep chaining the blind spell from a distance (dont want to get yourself) you will be targeted by their casters, if they have pets, the pets will come after you, lead them on a merry little run while the rest of your group picks them apart.  <br>
<br>
All kinds of thing you can add, Im sure.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usarvenosttz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SarvenostTZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/10/01 4:46:00 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid PvP tips</span><hr size=1> I've played a druid up to 48 on Tallon Zek. I know that my experiences will be less than applicable right now, but in a few months, once everyone that plays EQ as their life has had a chance to farm resist items, here's how it falls out:<br>
<br>
Don't expect to land a snare, a root, or almost anything magic based. When fighting equal level, it only takes 80magres to make you effectively impossible to snare (unless debuffed). When fighting people above or below you, the commonly accepted (at least among people I've talked to, and it seems to work from experience) formula is for every level you have over them, it's effectively -10 magic resist. So if you're fighting someone who has 6 levels with you, you're fighting at a big disadvantage.<br>
<br>
Everyone's weak resists are Disease and Poison. If you have those spells, use them. If you can buff those resists (yay druids), do it.<br>
<br>
About debuff spells working 150%, that's only stat debuffs. This doesn't affect snare or root landing at all. It does, however, make Tash especially nasty. Also Ro's Firey Sundering works well, lets you land all your DDs for the full 62.5%. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/10/01 7:47:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/rtfm.gif width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid PvP tips</span><hr size=1> Sarvenost says:  <b><i>Don't expect to land a snare, a root, or almost anything magic based.</b></i><br>
<br>
...except for the (bugged) stinging swarm line, which is for all practical purposes unresistable in PvP.  If you play your cards right with stacking, your opponent can be dying as he desparately tries to pumice his way out of it.<br>
<br>
As for direct damage, any spell that's <b>not</b> "all or nothing" (i.e., can do partial damage) is decent on newbies because their resists aren't too high.  But don't bother casting DD spells on any kind of healer unless you're going to finish them off with one -- you will burn more mana than they do.<br>
<br>
IN EQ PvP, be glad you're a druid.  You're basically unkillable unless you go linkdead, are gang-banged, or make a really stupid mistake. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://lag999.homestead.com/files/biggrin.gif width=15 height=15 BORDER=0> at: 7/10/01 7:48:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/11/01 5:21:06 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://astro.temple.edu/~fmoffat/img/small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid PvP tips</span><hr size=1> Let me state unequivocally that I'm not above making a really stupid mistake :-)<br>
<br>
Interesting tip on the Swarm line. I don't think I have to worry about pumice for people in my level range currently, most of us are dead flat broke just trying to buy spells. I need to get to 14 quick :-)<br>
<br>
Also, for the time being, resists aren't applicable, as Sarvenost noted. Most players are still lowbies, although some of the guilds are just leveling at frightening rates. <br>
<br>
I need to farm Alla's and and the other equipment sites for lower level resist gear. <br>
<br>
Keep talking, I like hearing it, even if it's just stories about fighting the enemy. SZ is a good time so far.<br>
<br>
I made the trek to NK last night, was trying to find some wisps in my level range (9th level) to see if I could nuke them into oblivion. I never did find any, but damn, it's freaky de-cloaking to fight, knowing I could get waxed at any minute by a real human. NK is a little tough right now, leaves me way low on mana and hp, so I think I'll stick to Misty for the moment...I really need a few more spells, as well.<br>
<br>
I saw a blue con goblin peon in Runnyeye on my way home, and pulled him to the Misty zone line. Those little buggers have *insane* regen! I thought he was getting healed, the way his hp bar was climbing. I had to zone after getting him to about 25% 3 times.<br>
<br>
Fun, fun, fun, can't wait to log back on :-) <p><b>Gallatin</b><p>
<font size=3>Everyone is entitled to their own wrong opinion</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usarvenosttz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SarvenostTZ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/11/01 7:56:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid PvP tips</span><hr size=1> Actually, I had forgotten about the Swarm line. Those are some of the most useful spells we have. They will land in PvP just as reliably as on mobs. They are so reliable that I'm inclined to think that they don't even actually check for resistances, they just have a flat rate for resists for everything (barring very special mobs). It's the only thing I can come up with, since they get resisted as often by an orc pawn as they do by a wurm.<br>
<br>
Generally, when going into PvP (at 30+), you'll want to try one Ensnare (it's a 1.8 cast time, you're really not losing much). If that is resisted, DoT them and start your DDs. If you have the opportunity later to snare them, go for it, otherwise just go without it.<br>
<br>
Best low lvl piece of resist gear? Shiny Brass Shield out of CrushBone. 10MR rules. Gets you towards that magic 80%. (BTW, at 60-65%, nobody will be able to snare you most of the time, but it will still stick, occasionally) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugallatin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gallatin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/11/01 8:03:05 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://astro.temple.edu/~fmoffat/img/small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid PvP tips</span><hr size=1> On this server, I've got about as much chance of seeing an SBS as I do seeing Nagafen in the next week :-) Off a good zone...I don't see them taking kindly to me waltzing in, although it does sound like a fun stealth op when I get to work early some morning...hmm, I really need SoW and See Invis soon :-) <p><b>Gallatin</b><p>
<font size=3>Everyone is entitled to their own wrong opinion</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uadiyencrowe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adiyen Crowe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(7/11/01 9:14:17 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Druid PvP tips</span><hr size=1> When you buff, your buffs in order of least important to most..<br>
usually i do,thorns, see invis, str, ac thorn shield, ice, fire, sow, sln, mr..<br>
<br>
sometimes i throw the disease, poison resists at the top.<br>
<br>
Then, drop the first thorn shield so you have an empty slot where dots etc can be dispelled from.<br>
<br>
Also.. remember cure poison gets rid of tash, and those Crimson potions you can buy at vendor's make you unmezzable.<br>
<br>
<br>
Adiyen Crowe<br>
55th Preserver<br>
