2) See invis<br>
3) Strength of Karana<br>
4) Circle of Winter<br>
5) Bladecoat<br>
6) Resist Disease<br>
7) Resist Poison<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Mask of the hunter<br>
9) Circle of Summer<br>
10) Regrowth of the Grove<br>
11) Resist Magic<br>
12) Levitate<br>
13) Protection of the Glades<br>
14) Spirit of the Wolf<br>
15) Normally I have another classes buff - symbol/clarity 2 or I'll just fill it with My damage shield.<br>
<br>
A few points.<br>
Why 15 buffs ? well dots/debuffs will always goto the first empty space, before i could fill my buff stack, i just clicked off firefist and see invis so any dots landing would go there and i could dispel them as i saw fit.<br>
<br>
Now i have 15 buffs I don't need to worry about it, they just overwrite my first useless buffs - quite often i'll get fighting a necro and they'll splurt me, then dispel me to try and remove my sow/buffs, only to remove their own dot...<br>
<br>
Why is CoW so early in my buff stack ? Well Malo is unresistable and overwrites the buff (Mala/Malo is a 60-70 debuff to MR/PR/FR/DR in PvP). This way if a shaman or a mage casts it on me I can just click of my first few buffs and dispel it rather than have it stuck deep in my buff stack.<br>
<br>
